{
  "stem": "7337.3",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "But [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] she had her wish.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "And then her professor actually operated her and removed her stomach.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "That's the first time that a stomach-- total stomach was removed from a patient in Europe.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] Unfortunately, it was too late and she died [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] shortly after that operation.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "She died in 1934.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 10 SECONDS] The-- she was very close-- she had two brothers, and she was very close to the older one who was-- he was a dental surgeon.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "And he used to come and visit us occasionally from Germany for a day or two.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "And then [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] she made him promise her that he would marry [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] when she died, and he married his girlfriend.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] And whilst we're talking about this uncle, in 1938, when we were already in South Africa, we heard that he had been taken into a concentration camp.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "And we got the Red Cross to trace him to Dachau.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 46,
      "text": "In those days, you could pay the Nazis 1,500 pounds, and buy a Jew out of a concentration camp.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we sent 1,500 round-- pounds to the-- through the Zionist Federation to the British consul in Hamburg, and he brought him out.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And he had him put onto a German boat that went to Palestine.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And he also had his wife taken from her apartment, and they met on this boat.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they came out in 1938 to Palestine, where he practiced for the rest of his life, until 1959, [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] as dental surgeon.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 9 SECONDS]",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My father, had-- he was one of 13 children.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] 11 were girls, and two were boys.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
